  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Social control is any mechanism by which a society enforces conformity to its norms. Law is only one such mechanism — and not always the most effective one. Gossip, shame, ostracism, economic pressure, professional norms, and family expectations all regulate behavior without legal intervention.",
  "keywords": "legalism",
